snippet.textDisplay: Hi, I am a 17 year old High School student from central Scotland. After finishing school this year I had partnered up with a charity called Project Trust, which sends recent school leavers abroad for a year to teach english to underprivileged children in developing countries. The country I would be going to is Honduras, which is perfect for me as the national language is Spanish and due to my dads Spanish heritage I speak fluent Spanish, the condition for the charity is that you need to fundraise £6200, this is to be done by the end of June, I was perfectly on track having just over £3000 at the end of February. I had planned a ceilidh and a coffee morning for my local community, which I was going to advertise through my second job where I make up the paper rounds for my town, by sliding leaflets in all the newspapers. All the proceeds I made from this were going towards a Kiltwalk, which is essentially a 23mile walk in a kilt (which you could do with me?). My issue is due to the recent coronavirus, I have had to cancel my upcoming events as it is too dangerous for the elderly members of the community. Therefore, I was wondering if you would be able to help me in any way? Love from Erik in Scotland
